<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="562" pageId="5" pageNumber="560" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1966,2027]" box="[151,757,1966,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="560">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1966,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="560">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 
<quantity box="[664,753,1966,1991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="560" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1966,2027]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="561" pageId="5" pageNumber="560">
Crown straw colored, with black spot on either side of median line closer to eyes, one square spot in middle; face upper part gray with black round spot on either side of median line closer to median line; frontoclypeus mainly black, yellowish in middle, anteclypeus black, lora and gena brownish, antennal fossa brownish. Pronotum gray, with three triangular spots on anterior margin and one spot on either side of median line and several brown stripes closer to posterior margin. Scutellum dark yellow, with median stripes and basal triangles dark brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,161,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K–L). Forewing hyaline with brown tinge, veins and apex of forewing dark brown, apex of clavus whitish. Mesepimeron black. Legs pale ochraceous, hind leg macrosetae brownish (
<figureCitation box="[992,1065,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
Figs. 
<number box="[1055,1065,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" value="1.0">
<date box="[1055,1065,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">1</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I–J).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" targetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1435,1923,1976]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1923,1945]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[288,545,1923,1944]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioceroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petaliformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[288,545,1923,1944]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">Idioceroides petaliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[556,640,1923,1944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,640,1923,1944]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Face without short setae adjacent to corresponding eye; rostrum short, not reaching hind coxae. Pronotum rugose. Scutellum about as long as pronotum and crown together (
<figureCitation box="[908,972,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,199,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,193,1705]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Flexocerus sinuatus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male; E, head and thorax of female, dorsal view; F, face of female; G, habitus of female, dorsal view; H, habitus of female, lateral view. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245573/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number box="[961,972,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
K). 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1076,188,213]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibiae with 
<number box="[1214,1284,188,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="23.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="22.0">22–24</number>
setae on row PD, 
<number box="[201,215,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="9.0">9</number>
setae on AD and 
<number box="[414,442,224,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="12.0">12</number>
setae on row AV. Other characters as in generic description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Male genitalia. Male pygofer elongate, broader in middle, compressed apically, with dense setae on lateral area, ventral margin convex. Subgenital plate broad, dorsal margin straight, ventral margin convex, with many setae on dorsal margin and lateral area, pointed apically (
<figureCitation box="[784,851,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1397,409,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number box="[836,851,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Valve broader than long, caudal margin rounded, shieldlike. Style with process on dorsal margin nearer base than apex; caudal part tapering apically, apex curved (
<figureCitation box="[159,228,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1397,409,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,228,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Connective T-shaped, stem slender and long. Aedeagus with preatrium well developed, dorsal apodeme short; shaft evenly curved dorsad, with lateral preapical flange bearing two pairs of long distally projecting spines, dorsal surface with pair of long retrorse preapical spines, apex in lateral view with shorter spine projecting anterad; gonopore subapical on ventral surface.(
<figureCitation box="[595,670,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1923,1945]" captionTargetBox="[208,1385,417,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1397,409,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Idioceroides petaliformis sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, valve; C, connective, ventral view; D, aedeagus, lateral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/245576/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
Figs. 
<number box="[655,670,512,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D–E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1394,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,752]" box="[199,1394,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,548,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="562">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet name refers to the flower like appearance of the aedeagus in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
